summary: In this context, decane and 3-xylene are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) being investigated for their pro-inflammatory potential. The study aims to assess the effects of various aliphatic and aromatic compounds, including decane and 3-xylene, on human lung epithelial cells. However, the specific interactions or comparative effects between decane and 3-xylene are not detailed, indicating a general association rather than a direct relationship.
